nd contributors explore ideas, concepts, and skills that will help human service workers, social workers, helping professionals, and policymakers deepen their understanding of cultural attitudes toward newly arrived immigrants and refugees, thus strengthening their ability to better serve an ethnically diverse clientele.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aEmigration and immigration lawzUnited States. 0aImmigrantszUnited States. 0aRefugeeszUnited States. 0aSocial work with immigrantszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aBalgopal, Pallassana R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBalgopal, Pallassana, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrancis, E. Aracelis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarger, Howard Jacob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevine, Joanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLongres, John F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayadas, Nazneen S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNimmagadda, Jayashree, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPatterson, Davis G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSegal, Uma A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044247240uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/balg1085640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231504188423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231504188.jpg  a978-3-11-044247-2  Columbia University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL